['Actually you can substitute x=6tan(*). Then
dx /d(*)=6(sec^2(*))d(*)
then dx=6(sec^2(*))d(*)
then integral becomes {6sec^2(*)d(*) /36(1/(1+tan^2(*))}
This gives integral of {sec^2(*)d(*)/6sec^2(*)}
Which gives integral of 1/6{d(*)}
